Pre-heat the #oven to 220 degrees and wash the @sweet potato{1}. Chop the potato in
half lengthways, then in half lengthways again. Chop into roughly 2cm cubes. Place
the sweet potato pieces on a #baking tray{}, drizzle over @olive oil{1%tbsp} and cook
in the oven for ~{15-20%minutes} until just cooked.

Roughly chop the @coriander{3} and the @jalapeño chilli{2}. Finely chop the
@spring onion{1} into micro-thin discs, separating the green and white parts.
Peel and finely chop the @red onion{1}. Chop the @cherry tomatoes{1} into quarters.

Heat @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a #non-stick frying pan{} on medium heat. Gently cook
all but a tbsp of the red onion for around ~{5%minutes} until soft. Stir in @salt{1/4%tsp}.
Add in the @smoked paprika{1/2%tsp} and continue to cook for ~{1%minute}.

Drain and thoroughly rinse the @organic black beans{1} before adding them to the pan.
Add the jalapeño chillies and another pinch of salt.

> Jalapeños are hot so add them according to taste!

Cook for ~{2%minutes} and then turn off the heat.

Add three quarters of the coriander. Thoroughly mix everything together a few grinds
of @black pepper{}. Lastly, stir in @spring onion whites{1%tsp} and squeeze in
@lime juice{1%tbsp}.

> You can add more of the spring onion according to personal taste.

Once the potatoes are soft enough to eat, remove them from the oven and turn your
#grill onto its highest setting. Pile the bean mixture onto the sweet potatoes.
Crumble three quarters of the @feta cheese{1} over the top and grill for ~{5%minutes}
or until nice and golden brown.

Toss together the tomatoes with the remaining coriander and a pinch of salt and
pepper. Drizzle over a little @olive oil{a little}, with a squeeze of @lime{1/2} and
the remaining tbsp of diced red onion.

> If you don't like raw onion, just gently cook it off in a frying pan first with
> a little oil or you can miss it out altogether.

Serve a big spoon of the bake with the greens of the spring onion for garnish, a bit
more crumbled feta, and the tomato salad on the side - Arriba!